VHDtool
==========

A tool to examine and manipulate VHD images. Initially
meant as a way to test dynamic VHD support in my
Linux kernel loop VHD parser support (yet doesn't
support dynamic VHDs, rofl).

Building
========

Builds on recent Linux (i.e. not RHEL5, *sigh*), and
needs libuuid (you probably have it).

To build:

$ make

Examples
========

Generate a 512-byte fixed VHD:

$ vhdtool -s 512 test.vhd

Generate a 50 sector fixed VHD:

$ vhdtool -s 512s test.vhd

Valid size modifiers are:
b/B/*nothing* -> bytes
k/K           -> kilobytes
m/M           -> megabytes
g/G           -> gigabytes
t/T           -> terabytes
s/S           -> sectors

